The article is a statement by the President of the United States on the death of Japanese citizen Haruna Yukawa, who was murdered by the terrorist group ISIL. The President strongly condemns the brutal act and offers condolences to the people of Japan. The statement also calls for the immediate release of Kenji Goto and all other remaining hostages. The United States stands in solidarity with Japan and supports its commitment to peace and development in the region. The President emphasizes that both countries will work together to bring the perpetrators to justice and will continue to take action to degrade and defeat ISIL.